.TH BVAULT 1 "May 2026" "bvault 0.3.2" "BastionVault Manual"
.SH NAME
bvault \- BastionVault command-line client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bvault
.RI [ subcommand ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bvault
is the command-line client for a BastionVault server. It speaks the
Vault-compatible HTTP API and can also be used to start, init, and
unseal a server instance.
.PP
The CLI is configured by the
.B BASTIONVAULT_ADDR
and
.B BASTIONVAULT_TOKEN
environment variables (a fallback to the equivalent
.B VAULT_ADDR
/
.B VAULT_TOKEN
is honoured for compatibility).
.SH COMMON SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B server
Run a BastionVault server.
.TP
.B operator init
Initialise a freshly provisioned server, generating root token and
unseal keys.
.TP
.B operator unseal
Submit one unseal share. Repeat until the seal threshold is met.
.TP
.B status
Show the seal / leader / health state of the configured server.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/bvault/config.hcl
Default config path used by the official container image.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bv-ssh-helper (1),
the BastionVault online documentation at
.UR https://github.com/ffquintella/BastionVault
.UE .
